{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn the best practices for enhancing the functionality and performance of your web content on iOS, whether it is in a website or native app. Gain proficiency with the remote Web Inspector, see how to reduce the overall memory footprint of your web content, and dive deep into the details of WebKit drawing and compositing to ensure that scrolling and animations are always smooth. Discover new features in iOS 6 that allow for tighter integration between apps and websites, enabling deep linking to content within an already-installed app or letting users purchase an app with just a few taps."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference"}]}]}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2012\/601\/"}},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC12","role":"sampleCode","title":"Optimizing Web Content in UIWebViews and Websites on iOS"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC12-601-Optimizing-Web-Content-in-UIWebViews-and-Websites-on-iOS"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"kind":"article","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc12-601-optimizing-web-content-in-uiwebviews-and-websites-on-ios"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentatio